snippet.textDisplay:
About time, I hope AMD makes a dual Vega refresh card, well I guess technically if it's on 7nm it isn't just a refresh, would also be nice to see Nvidia put out a lineup with decent memory bus sizes, we're too far along in GPU progress to still be seeing cards with 92-128 bit memory bus, and 256 on most cards above the entry level.

I've seen just how much poor memory bandwidth, or just limited can affect performance, it isn't pretty, and going with a 512 or more bit memory bus shouldn't be an issue.
